source: crates/acetone-cli/tests/help_snapshots.rs
expression: stdout(&out)
---
The acetone command-line workbench

Usage: acetone [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  init              Create a new acetone repository
  status            Show the current branch, head commit and workspace state
  commit            Turn the workspace's staged changes into a commit
  log               Show commit history, newest first
  branch            List branches, or create one
  checkout          Switch the checked-out branch
  diff              Show the graph-level difference between two versions
  merge             Merge another version into the current branch
  resolve           Resolve a merge in progress by taking one whole side
  declare-label     Declare a primary label's key and constraints (schema)
  declare-rel-type  Declare a relationship type (schema)
  declare-index     Declare a property index over `(label, properties)`
  reindex           Rebuild every declared index from the nodes map
  schema            Show the declared schema — labels and keys, relationship types and indexes
  import            Import a source file into the graph
  export            Export a graph version as per-label and per-type tables
  query             Run an openCypher read query against the graph [aliases: cypher]
  shell             Start an interactive Cypher shell (readline REPL)
  fsck              Verify repository integrity
  gc                Consolidate the object store into a packfile
  migrate           Rewrite all history under new chunk parameters
  put-node          Insert or replace a node (plumbing; single-column keys only)
  get-node          Look up a node by label and key
  put-edge          Insert or replace an edge (plumbing; no properties, no discriminator)
  list-nodes        List nodes, in key order
  rekey             Change a node's key (single-column keys)
  help              Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --repo <REPO>
          Path to the repository. Ignored by `init` when it is given its own PATH argument
          
          [default: .]

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

  -V, --version
          Print version

Command groups:
  Everyday      init, status, commit, log, branch, checkout, diff, merge, resolve
  Schema        declare-label, declare-rel-type, declare-index, reindex, schema
  Data & query  import, export, query, shell
  Maintenance   fsck, gc, migrate
  Plumbing      put-node, get-node, put-edge, list-nodes, rekey

Relationship to git (an acetone version IS a git commit):
  Use acetone, not git   commit, merge, resolve, checkout, declare-*, reindex,
                         import, export, fsck, gc, migrate — the git equivalents
                         would write commits acetone cannot read.
  Either works           log, status, diff, branch — acetone's are graph-aware;
                         plain git still works on the same repo.
  Git only (transport)   clone, fetch, push, pull, remote — no acetone command;
                         any git remote is backup and transport.
